If movies are ranked by how much they pay tribute to americas armed forces this is an 11. If movies are ranked by their entertainment value as a whole this movie is a 3.

"Can't complain about acting as these are real navy seals playing the roles"

This is an action movie so yes I can complain about the acting. There are plenty of realistic war movies with excellent casting. "Blackhawk Down" comes to mind. There are also excellent *documentaries* about the military and the SEALs specifically. "U.S. Navy SEALs: The Silent Option" is one. This movie is not a documentary so "realness" is not something I care about.

Yes, these are real SEALs ... I get it. That doesn't make the plot better than it is, or the acting better than it is, or the character development better than it is. Character development has nothing to do with the actors ... Im not shitting on them for the failures of the script. They are only responsible for the bad acting and I forgive them for being bad actors as they are SEALs by trade, not actors. It's not their fault the movie turned out to be crap ... I'm sure they are badass at being SEALs so who cares if they can't act. I am not forgiving the movie for being bad ... it's not a 10 or an 11 or w/e the hell rating unless you evaluate it as a propaganda piece for recruiting more SEALs.

Please note I am not using propaganda as some kind of negative term. This movie is one big recruiting video for the Navy SEALs which is *TOTALLY* fine except it's a bad movie when compared to other action movies. That's all sorry for the rant :)
